The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 Utpal Chatterjee scalped five for 68 to help Sporting Union beat Aikya Sammilani by 81 runs in a CAB league match on Monday. Sporting will take on Calcutta Customs in the quarter finals. Chasing 291, Aikya were bowled out for 209. Abhishek Das (56) was the top scorer. In a CAB knock out one-day match, East Bengal defeated Aryan by 75 runs to book a quarter final berth. Batting first, East Bengal managed 215 for eight in 45 overs. Aryan were restricted to 140 for six.

 About 120 boys and girls (aged 6-12) will be trained at the IOC BTTA-organised table tennis summer coaching camp..

 Sanjay Sood recorded a hole -in-one at the 13th hole of the Royal Calcutta Golf Club (RCGC) course on May 4. This is according to an RCGC release.

 FOOTBALL: National League; East Bengal vs Mahindra United at Salt Lake from 7 pm.




